1st open settings and click adavanced then click developers then turn on do what you need to do 
2nd type "echo "deb https://download.opensuse.org/repositories/home:/strycore/Debian_11/ ./" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/lutris.list" (this will get the parckage needed for the rest of the installment") now press enter
3rd type "wget -q https://download.opensuse.org/repositories/home:/strycore/Debian_11/Release.key -O- | sudo tee /etc/apt/trusted.gpg.d/lutris.asc" (this will get the package to install lutris) now press enter
4th type "sudo apt update" (this will update the linux files and other important but dont need to know files" press enter now
5th type "sudo apt install lutris"" (this will install lutris) now press enter
